#. type: Hash Value: headerList mixedWbClassAddendum
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_sR.yaml:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Additionally, this dataset includes data from countries whose economies belong to different income groups, as defined by the World Bank (%s). This means that the healthcare systems and infrastructure of the included countries may vary considerably, which could further affect the interpretation and comparability of some indicators."
msgstr ""

#. type: Hash Value: headerList multiCountryDatasetHint
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_sR.yaml:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "This report aggregates data from neonatal departments in several countries. While ideally a single-country report would be preferable, aggregating data across multiple countries is pragmatically necessary when sufficient participation from a single country is not available. This means that, while it reflects a broad spectrum of care structures, it is only suitable as a benchmark to a somewhat limited extent due to the sometimes very different healthcare systems and the resources available there. The aim of NeoIPC Surveillance is therefore always to provide departments with a relevant national or regional report, provided that a sufficient number of departments in the respective region participate in the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Hash Value: headerList singleCountryDatasetHint
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_sR.yaml:1
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "This report presents data from neonatal units in a single country. This means that, because of the relative homogeneity of the healthcare system, it is in principle a good benchmark. However, it should be noted that only a proportion of neonatal units in a country actually participate in NeoIPC Surveillance. Since participation is voluntary, these are typically hospitals that have a particular interest in infection prevention and are willing and able to provide the resources required for surveillance."
msgid "This report presents data from neonatal departments in a single country. Because of the relative homogeneity of the healthcare system, it is in principle a good benchmark. However, it should be noted that only a proportion of neonatal departments in a country actually participate in NeoIPC Surveillance. Since participation is voluntary, these are typically hospitals that have a particular interest in infection prevention and are willing and able to provide the resources required for surveillance. The information presented here can therefore not fully describe the situation in the individual countries."
msgstr "Este informe presenta datos de unidades neonatales de un solo país. Esto significa que, debido a la relativa homogeneidad del sistema sanitario, en principio es un buen punto de referencia. Sin embargo, cabe señalar que solo una parte de las unidades neonatales de un país participan realmente en la vigilancia NeoIPC. Dado que la participación es voluntaria, se trata normalmente de hospitales que tienen un interés particular en la prevención de infecciones y que están dispuestos y son capaces de proporcionar los recursos necesarios para la vigilancia."

