#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_introduction.Rmd:2
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "This document is a reference report on the NeoIPC Surveillance. It contains information relating to nosocomial infections, their causative infectious agents, and the associated risk and protective factors in high-risk neonates which was collected by partners from multiple neonatology departments participating in the NeoIPC Surveillance. The following numbers provide an overview of the current data set. If you are interested in the surveillance definitions, data collection methods and sheets, please refer to the [surveillance resources on the NeoIPC website](https://neoipc.org/surveillance/resources/).\n"
msgid "This document is a reference report on the NeoIPC Surveillance. It contains information relating to nosocomial infections, their causative infectious agents, and the associated risk and protective factors in high-risk neonates which was collected by partners from multiple neonatology departments participating in the NeoIPC Surveillance. If you are interested in the surveillance definitions, data collection methods and sheets, please refer to the [surveillance resources on the NeoIPC website](https://neoipc.org/surveillance/resources/).\n"
msgstr "Este documento es un informe de referencia sobre la vigilancia NeoIPC. Contiene información relacionada con las infecciones nosocomiales, sus agentes infecciosos causantes y los factores de riesgo y protección asociados en neonatos de alto riesgo, recopilada por socios de múltiples departamentos de neonatología que participan en la vigilancia NeoIPC. Las siguientes cifras ofrecen una visión general del conjunto de datos actual. Si está interesado en las definiciones de vigilancia, los métodos de recopilación de datos y las hojas de datos, consulte los recursos de vigilancia en el sitio web de NeoIPC.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_introduction.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following numbers provide an overview of the current data set. A patient record represents an individual patient; patient admissions count separately each admission episode during the surveillance period, so a patient who was readmitted will have more than one admission. Patient days are the cumulative days of surveillance across all patients.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_introduction.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rates in this report use different denominators depending on the metric. Incidence density rates and risk and protective factor rates are expressed per patient days. Infectious agent detection rates and resistant pathogen infection rates are expressed per infections in which a pathogen was detected. Surgical procedure rates are expressed per patients. Each table's formula footnote specifies the exact denominator used.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_patient_population.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "As the process, although supported by various tools, relies on the collection, interpretation and monitoring of information by qualified professionals, NeoIPC surveillance is currently being targeted at the most common nosocomial infections in high-risk neonates, in order to make it sustainable in a continuous manner in as many settings as possible. This means that patients with a birth weight below 1500 g and/or a gestational age below 32 weeks at the time of birth are included into the surveillance database if they are admitted to a participating neonatology department within the first 120 days of life. In combination with the filter settings specified above, this results in the composition of the patient population shown in @fig-bw and @fig-ga.\n"
msgstr "Dado que el proceso, aunque cuenta con el apoyo de diversas herramientas, se basa en la recopilación, interpretación y seguimiento de la información por parte de profesionales cualificados, la vigilancia NeoIPC se centra actualmente en las infecciones nosocomiales más comunes en neonatos de alto riesgo, con el fin de que sea sostenible de forma continua en el mayor número posible de entornos. Esto significa que los pacientes con un peso al nacer inferior a 1500 g y/o una edad gestacional inferior a 32 semanas en el momento del nacimiento se incluyen en la base de datos de vigilancia si son ingresados en un departamento de neonatología participante en los primeros 120 días de vida. En combinación con los ajustes de filtro especificados anteriormente, esto da como resultado la composición de la población de pacientes que se muestra en @fig-bw y @fig-ga.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_nosocomial_infections.Rmd:2
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Nosocomial infections represent the primary endpoint of NeoIPC surveillance. In @tbl-incidence-density-rates, the incidence densities of sepsis/BSI, pneumonia and necrotising enterocolitis, as well as the combined endpoint 'severe infection', are displayed. Overall `r dR$numberOfSevereInfections` severe infections were recorded in `r dR$numberOfPatients` infants resulting in an average number of `r dR$averageSevereInfectionsPerPatient` infections per patient.\n"
msgid "Nosocomial infections represent the primary endpoint of NeoIPC surveillance. In`r dR$refIDRTable` the incidence densities of sepsis/BSI, pneumonia and necrotising enterocolitis, as well as the combined endpoint 'severe infection', are displayed. Overall `r dR$numberOfSevereInfections` severe infections were recorded in `r dR$numberOfPatients` infants resulting in an average number of `r dR$averageSevereInfectionsPerPatient` infections per patient.\n"
msgstr "Las infecciones nosocomiales representan el criterio de valoración principal de la vigilancia del NeoIPC. En @tbl-incidence-density-rates se muestran las densidades de incidencia de sepsis/BSI, neumonía y enterocolitis necrotizante, así como el criterio de valoración combinado «infección grave». En total, se registraron `r dR$numberOfSevereInfections` infecciones graves en `r dR$numberOfPatients` lactantes, lo que supone una media de `r dR$averageSevereInfectionsPerPatient` infecciones por paciente.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_nosocomial_infections.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "`r sR$benchmarking_guidance`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_nosocomial_infections.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "`r if (nzchar(dR$refDevAssTable)) paste0(\"Device-associated infections can be found in\", dR$refDevAssTable, \".\")`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_infectious_agents.Rmd:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Epidemiology of the infectious agents causing nosocomial infections in neonatology is complex and there is a lot of potential for bias. While low diagnostic sensitivity (low blood volume) and specificity (contamination) are a general problem in the neonatal population, the lack of availability of some or all means of microbiological diagnostics, or the lack of financial resources can have a strong effect on the detection rates in resource-constrained settings.\n"
msgstr "La epidemiología de los agentes infecciosos que causan infecciones nosocomiales en neonatología es compleja y existe un gran potencial de sesgo. Si bien la baja sensibilidad diagnóstica (bajo volumen sanguíneo) y la especificidad (contaminación) son un problema general en la población neonatal, la falta de disponibilidad de algunos o todos los medios de diagnóstico microbiológico, o la falta de recursos financieros, pueden tener un fuerte efecto en las tasas de detección en entornos con recursos limitados.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_infectious_agents.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "<!-- When comparing data with the information on pathogens presented in @tbl-agent-per-infection-rate and information on drug resistance in @tbl-abr-infection-rate, please also have a look at the infectious agent detection rates presented in @tbl-infectious-agent-detection-rate and the antibiotic resistance test rates in @tbl-resistance-test-rate. -->\n"
msgstr "<!-- Al comparar los datos con la información sobre patógenos presentada en @tbl-agent-per-infection-rate y la información sobre resistencia a los medicamentos en @tbl-abr-infection-rate, consulte también las tasas de detección de agentes infecciosos presentadas en @tbl-infectious-agent-detection-rate y las tasas de pruebas de resistencia a los antibióticos en @tbl-resistance-test-rate. -->\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_infectious_agents.Rmd:5
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "In total, `r dR$numberOfInfectiousAgents` infectious agents were detected in the `r dR$numberOfInfectionsWithAgent` infections that were reported to have yielded at least one agent from either the primary infection and/or the secondary bloodstream infection resulting from it (@tbl-agent-per-infection-rate). These `r dR$numberOfInfectionsWithAgent` diagnostic-positive infections out of `r dR$overallNumberOfInfections` overall infections represent an Infectious Agent Detection Rate of `r dR$infectiousAgentDetectionRate` per 100 infections (@tbl-infectious-agent-detection-rate).\n"
msgid "In total, `r dR$numberOfInfectiousAgents` infectious agents were detected in the `r dR$numberOfInfectionsWithAgent` infections that were reported to have yielded at least one agent from either the primary infection and/or the secondary bloodstream infection resulting from it`r dR$refAgentPerInfTable`. These `r dR$numberOfInfectionsWithAgent` diagnostic-positive infections out of `r dR$overallNumberOfInfections` overall infections represent an Infectious Agent Detection Rate of `r dR$infectiousAgentDetectionRate` per 100 infections`r dR$refDetectionTable`.\n"
msgstr "En total, se detectaron `r dR$numberOfInfectiousAgents` agentes infecciosos en las `r dR$numberOfInfectionsWithAgent` infecciones que, según se informó, habían producido al menos un agente, ya fuera de la infección primaria o de la infección secundaria del torrente sanguíneo resultante de ella (@tbl-agent-per-infection-rate). Estas `r dR$numberOfInfectionsWithAgent` infecciones con diagnóstico positivo de un total de `r dR$overallNumberOfInfections` infecciones representan una tasa de detección de agentes infecciosos del `r dR$infectiousAgentDetectionRate` por cada 100 infecciones (@tbl-infectious-agent-detection-rate).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_risk_and_protective_factors.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next to the inherent risk factors gestational age and birth weight there are also a number of expositional factors that influence the risk of an infant to acquire a multi-drug-resistant pathogen or to develop an infection. @tbl-risk-density-rates shows the presence of these factors in the NeoIPC Surveillance population.\n"
msgstr "Además de los factores de riesgo inherentes, como la edad gestacional y el peso al nacer, también hay una serie de factores de exposición que influyen en el riesgo de que un bebé contraiga un patógeno multirresistente o desarrolle una infección. @tbl-risk-density-rates muestra la presencia de estos factores en la población de vigilancia del NeoIPC.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_surgery.Rmd:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "`r dR$numberOfSurgicalDepartments` of the partner departments in this dataset (`r dR$proportionOfSurgicalDepartments`) recorded a total of `r dR$numberOfSurgicalProcedures` surgical procedures performed on `r dR$numberOfSurgicalPatients` neonates, resulting in an average number of `r dR$numberOfSurgicalProceduresPerPatient` operations per surgical patient during the surveillance period.\n"
msgstr "`r dR$numberOfSurgicalDepartments` de los departamentos asociados a este conjunto de datos (`r dR$proportionOfSurgicalDepartments` %) registraron un total de `r dR$numberOfSurgicalProcedures` procedimientos quirúrgicos realizados a `r dR$numberOfSurgicalPatients` neonatos, lo que supone una media de `r dR$numberOfSurgicalProceduresPerPatient` operaciones por paciente quirúrgico durante el periodo de vigilancia.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_surgery.Rmd:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Due to the low number of surgical site infections in this dataset (n = `r dR$numberOfSurgicalSiteInfections`) we are not currently calculating their infection rates, but @tbl-surgical-procedure-rates provides an overview of the categories of procedures performed on neonates.\n"
msgstr "Debido al bajo número de infecciones del sitio quirúrgico en este conjunto de datos (n = `r dR$numberOfSurgicalSiteInfections`), actualmente no estamos calculando sus tasas de infección, pero @tbl-surgical-procedure-rates ofrece una visión general de las categorías de procedimientos realizados en neonatos.\n"

