#. type: Title ##
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solutions_intro.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Solutions {#sec-solutions}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solutions_intro.Rmd:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Since the NeoIPC Surveillance currently uses the Tracker Capture App in DHIS2 for managing patient data, the [DHIS2 user documentation for Tracker Capture](https://docs.dhis2.org/en/use/user-guides/dhis-core-version-240/tracking-individual-level-data/tracker-capture.html) applies in addition to the documentation provided here.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0001.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Patient Record Does Not Have an Enrolment {#sec-problem-details-1}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0001.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "This problem typically occurs when someone has tried to delete a patient's data (a patient record) but has only deleted the patient enrolment instead.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0001.Rmd:8
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"What remains is a patient record without patient enrolment, which exists in the system as a data orphan.\n"
"These patient records will not appear in the list of registered patients and their data cannot be listed in any reports, as most of the information required for analysis is missing.\n"
"However, if you try to enter a new patient with the same NeoIPC Patient ID, the system will recognise that this ID is already being used by a different patient and will reject the entry.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0001.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Depending on whether you want to continue using the data entered in the patient record or not, you have different options for resolving this situation. However, for both, you first have to open the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard of the patient record, which is not so easy for patient records without registration using the standard DHIS2 tools.\n"
"If you do not yet know how this works, please read @sec-solution-1.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0001.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have opened the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard of the patient record and do not want to keep the data, you can delete the patient record completely (see @sec-solution-2).\n"
"If you want to keep the data and include the patient in NeoIPC Surveillance, you can instead create a patient enrolment for the patient record (see @sec-solution-3).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0002.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Patient Record Has a Completed Surveillance End Form but the Enrolment Is Still Active {#sec-problem-details-2}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0002.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When you complete the surveillance end form, you should normally also complete the enrolment to mark the case as complete and ready for analysis and to protect it from accidental changes.\n"
"If you do not do this, the data for the patient in question will not be included in your analyses.\n"
"The easiest way to do this is to click 'Complete event and enrollment' in the dialogue box that appears after clicking 'Complete' in the surveillance end form. If you want to complete an enrolment afterwards and don't know how to do it, please follow the instructions in @sec-solution-4.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0003.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Admission Date in the Admission Form Differs From the Admission Date in the Enrolment {#sec-problem-details-3}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0003.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The NeoIPC Surveillance Platform requires a patient's admission date for internal calculations. The date must be present twice, once in the patient enrolment and once in the admission form (see @fig-the-two-admission-dates).\n"
"Normally, the exception form automatically takes the admission date from the patient registration.\n"
"There is also an input validation that prevents you from completing an admission form if the admission date does not match the admission date in the patient registration.\n"
"But you can change the admission date in the patient registration and confirm the change in the warning dialogue that appears (see @fig-warning-enrolment-admission-date).\n"
"The system can make erroneous calculations if it has two different admission dates for the same patient registration. Therefore, this must be prevented.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0003.Rmd:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please ensure that the correct admission date for the patient in question is entered in both the 'Admission date' field of the enrolment form and the 'Admission date' field of the admission form (see @sec-solution-6).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0003.Rmd:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The two input fields for the admission date must match](img/fig-the-two-admission-dates.png){#fig-the-two-admission-dates fig-alt=\"A screenshot in which two input fields for the admission date are highlighted by framing and marked with arrows\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0003.Rmd:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "![If you subsequently change an admission date in the patient registration, a warning dialogue appears](img/fig-warning-enrolment-admission-date.png){#fig-warning-enrolment-admission-date fig-alt=\"A dialogue with the title 'Admission date' and the text 'Updating this date might require further action from you. Events in this program have been scheduled based on this date, but these events will not be rescheduled automatically. Do you want to continue with the date update?' and the buttons 'Cancel' and 'OK'\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0004.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Date of the End of the Surveillance Is Earlier Than the Date of Admission in the Admission Form {#sec-problem-details-4}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0004.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When a patient's surveillance has ended, the date on which this happened must be entered on the Surveillance End form. Naturally, the earliest the surveillance can end is on the day it started, but not before.\n"
"In order for the system to calculate the denominator data and determine the patient's risk of infection, both the admission date and the surveillance end date must be entered correctly.\n"
"If this error occurs, you have either entered an incorrect admission date or an incorrect end of surveillance date.\n"
"To correct the admission date, please refer to @sec-solution-6. To correct the discharge date, see @sec-solution-7.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0005.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Patient Record’s Admission Form Is Not Completed {#sec-problem-details-5}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0005.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For each inpatient stay of a patient to be included in NeoIPC Surveillance, an enrolment must be created on the NeoIPC Surveillance platform.\n"
"This must always include a completed admission form in addition to the patient information.\n"
"This form is automatically created and opened when a patient is enrolled and should be completed and closed immediately (see @sec-solution-8) so that the data is available for internal calculations and analysis.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0006.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Patient Record Has a Completed Enrolment but the Surveillance End Form Is Not Completed {#sec-problem-details-6}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0006.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The surveillance end form is a mandatory form that must always be completed and closed before the patient enrolment is completed so that the data can be analysed later.\n"
"The data of a patient record without a surveillance end form cannot be included in analyses because the most important denominator data for calculating the rates is missing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0006.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please reopen the enrolment (see @sec-solution-5), fill in the surveillance end form, complete it (see @sec-solution-8) and then complete the patient record again (see @sec-solution-4).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0007.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Patient Record Contains a Completed Patient Enrolment or Surveillance End Form, but an Event Form Is Not Completed {#sec-problem-details-7}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0007.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When you have ended surveillance for a patient and completed enrolment, you should have all the information you need to apply the NeoIPC Surveillance definitions and to fill out and complete event forms that you have started, or to delete them if the definitions are not met.\n"
"Since input validation only occurs when forms are completed, data from incomplete forms cannot be included in analyses.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0007.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please complete the form (see @sec-solution-8).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0008.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Patient Record Contains an Event Form With a Date That Is Not Within the Time Frame of a Documented Admission {#sec-problem-details-8}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0008.Rmd:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The surveillance period for a patient enrolled in the NeoIPC Surveillance begins on admission and ends when the patient is discharged or dies.\n"
"Risk factors and infections are only recorded and documented in the NeoIPC Surveillance platform during this period.\n"
"This approach naturally means that all documented events (infections, surgical procedures) must have occurred between the date of admission and the date on which surveillance ends.\n"
"An event form with a date that does not fall within this time interval indicates either an input error or a misunderstanding of the intended procedure. The error is not necessarily in the form itself. An incorrect admission date or an incorrect date in the Surveillance-End form can also cause this error.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0008.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Please check the relevant data and correct the incorrect date (see @sec-solution-6 and @sec-solution-7).\n"
"If you have started an event form and at the end of the surveillance you find that the criteria of the NeoIPC Surveillance Definitions are not met, please delete the form (see @sec-solution-12).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0009.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Patient Record Contains an Enrolment Whose Time Interval Overlaps With That of Another Enrolment {#sec-problem-details-9}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0009.Rmd:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The majority of patients included in NeoIPC have only one hospital stay during the observation period, which starts with the first admission (usually at birth) and ends with discharge.\n"
"Only in a few cases are patients readmitted to hospital after discharge.\n"
"For this situation, the NeoIPC surveillance platform has the concept of enrolments, which allows patients who are readmitted after discharge to be included in the surveillance for a second (and third, fourth, etc.) time.\n"
"Naturally, the time intervals in which a patient is treated as an inpatient cannot overlap, and it follows that a new enrolment in the NeoIPC Surveillance platform can only start on the day after the last discharge at the earliest (in case a patient is discharged and readmitted on the same day, we ignore the discharge).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0009.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the case mentioned in the error message, there are multiple enrolments with overlapping surveillance periods (the period between the admission date and the surveillance end date). This may be due to either an input error in one of the date values or a misunderstanding of the purpose of the enrolment.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0009.Rmd:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please correct any incorrect dates (see @sec-solution-6) or delete any redundant enrolments (see @sec-solution-13) so that there is exactly one enrolment for each of the patient's hospital stays.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0010.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Number of Patient Days Does Not Match the Calculated Value {#sec-problem-details-10}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0010.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The patient days value entered in the End of Surveillance form is automatically calculated from the end of surveillance date and the admission date of the enrolment.\n"
"The number of patient days is one of the most important pieces of information for calculating rates in various analyses, and is also used to validate entries in several other fields. For example, the number of device days (CVC, PVC, ventilation, ...) cannot be greater than the number of patient days, which is checked during entry.\n"
"For these reasons, it is very important that the value for patient days is correct.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0010.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If this error message appears in the validation report, we have found that the stored value for patient days is not correct.\n"
"There can be two reasons for this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0010.Rmd:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "an error in our automatic calculation prior to `r format(lubridate::date(\"2024-08-21\"), format = \"%x\")` has caused the patient days value to be one day too low.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0010.Rmd:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "the admission date of the enrolment was changed after the end of surveillance form was completed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0010.Rmd:16
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As for the first reason, we are truly sorry, because it is a problem that we have caused and that is creating work for you.\n"
"Normally we would do everything possible to avoid this, and in the case of automatically calculated values this would be possible in principle - despite our basic policy of never changing the values entered by our partners without consultation - but unfortunately in this case the validation of the entries sometimes leads to an additional problem that we cannot solve ourselves with the information available to us.\n"
"For example, in some cases you may want to enter the same number of days ('device days') as the number of patient days for certain risk or protective factors (e.g. there are regular cases where the number of human milk days is the same as the number of patient days). In these cases, the value for the corresponding device days would also have to be adjusted, which we cannot do because we do not know the true value.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0010.Rmd:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "The second reason described above also has the input validation problem described in the previous section, which explains why the NeoIPC Surveillance Platform does not simply recalculate the value automatically when the admission date of the enrolment is changed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0010.Rmd:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Regardless of the cause of the problem, please update the patient days value in the Surveillance End form (see @sec-solution-11) and then check if other values need to be updated and adjust them if necessary.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Surgical Site Infection Did Not Occur During the Follow-Up Period of a Surgical Procedure {#sec-problem-details-11}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After surgery, patients are followed up as part of NeoIPC Surveillance for surgical site infections.\n"
"The follow-up period is defined as follows (the day of surgery is day 1):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:9
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Surgical site infection"
msgid "Superficial incisional infection: 30 days\n"
msgstr "Infección superficial de la incisión: 30 días\n"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deep incisional infection: 30 days or 90 days if an implant was inserted\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Organ/space infection: 30 days or 90 days if an implant was inserted\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "If this message appears in the validation report, the specified patient record contains a form for a surgical site infection, but not for a surgical procedure in the 30 or 90 days prior to that, as defined above.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "There may be different reasons for this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "A form was created for the surgical procedure, but the period of time between the procedure and the infection is too long.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    It is very unlikely that the infection is still related to the procedure after such a long time.\n"
"    Please check the documented findings again carefully and, if necessary, consult with the treating neonatologist and/or surgeon.\n"
"    If you still believe that this is a surgical site infection, please contact us (e.g. via our [support email address](mailto:NeoIPC-Support@charite.de)).\n"
"    If you have verified that it is not a surgical site infection, please delete the event form (see @sec-solution-12).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:22
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Not a surgical procedure"
msgid "No form has been created for the surgical procedure\n"
msgstr "No se ha creado ningún formulario para la intervención quirúrgica.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Please create an event form for the surgical procedure in the NeoIPC Surveillance platform (see @sec-solution-14), fill it out and complete it (see @sec-solution-8).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "The date for the surgical procedure or surgical site infection was entered incorrectly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0011.Rmd:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Please correct the erroneous date in the corresponding event form (see @sec-solution-7).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0012.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Manually Entered Pathogen Cannot Be Assigned {#sec-problem-details-12}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0012.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Since the pathogen list of the NeoIPC Surveillance Platform cannot contain all potential infectious agents occurring worldwide, we have created the option of adding pathogens that are not in the database as free text.\n"
"When this happens, we try to find out which pathogen it is, add it to the database and then assign the pathogen entered as free text to this new pathogen so that it can be grouped and analysed in the future.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0012.Rmd:8
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If this message appears in the validation report, we were unable to find out which pathogen (species, genus, family) is involved for the free text entered and were therefore unable to make a meaningful assignment.\n"
"As a result, the pathogen entered cannot appear in analyses or the reference data report.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0012.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "If in doubt, please consult your microbiological laboratory or try to find the correct pathogen using taxonomic databases such as [LPSN](https://www.bacterio.net/), [MycoBank](https://www.mycobank.org/) or [ICTV](https://ictv.global/taxonomy) and inform us so that we can include it in the database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0013.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Sum of All Antibiotic Substance Days Is Less Than the Total Number of Antibiotic Days {#sec-problem-details-13}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0013.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the Surveillance End form, the number of days on which a patient received (any) antibiotic treatment (antibiotic days) and the number of days on which each antibiotic substance was used (substance days) are recorded.\n"
"By nature, the number of antibiotic days must be less than or equal to the value obtained by adding all substance days.\n"
"Unfortunately, the input validation that checks this does not work reliably and can be bypassed, which leads to this error message in the validation report.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0013.Rmd:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please reopen the Surveillance End form (see @sec-solution-9) and enter the correct values for the individual substance days or the correct value for the antibiotic days.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0014.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Surgical Procedure Has an Invalid ICHI Code {#sec-problem-details-14}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0014.Rmd:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The stratification of surgical procedures in NeoIPC Surveillance is complicated by the lack of an internationally used coding system for surgical and procedural procedures.\n"
"Although many countries use variants of the WHO's ‘International Classification Of Procedures In Medicine’ (ICPM), almost all of them have national variants, making international comparisons difficult.\n"
"For this reason, when developing the NeoIPC Surveillance methods, we have decided to use the International Classification of Health Interventions (ICHI), which is currently being developed by the WHO in connection with ICD-11.\n"
"The disadvantage of this decision is that none of our partners can use their familiar national coding system for procedures. The advantage, however, is that we can rely on a modern and very comprehensive coding system that allows us to group and analyse different groups of procedures in a meaningful way.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0014.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please always enter valid ICHI codes in the ‘Main procedure code (ICHI)’ and ‘Side procedure code (ICHI)’ fields.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0014.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can find these codes by entering the English name of the procedure (or part of it) in the ‘Search’ field at the top left of the ICHI Reference Classification at https://icd.who.int/dev11/l-ichi/en.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0014.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have any problems finding the correct code, please contact us and we will be happy to help.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0014.Rmd:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To correct the reported error, please open the form (see @sec-solution-15) and enter the ICHI code for the procedure instead of the existing code.\n"
"If the form has already been completed, it will need to be reopened for editing (see @sec-solution-9). If the patient registration has also already been completed, you will also need to reopen it for editing beforehand (see @sec-solution-5).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0015.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Patient Record Has a Completed Enrolment but no Surveillance End Form {#sec-problem-details-15}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0015.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The Surveillance End form is a mandatory form that must always be present before you complete the enrollment so that the data can be analysed afterwards.\n"
"This error message will appear in the validation report if the patient record contains a completed enrolment without a Surveillance End Form.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0015.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please open the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard of the patient record (see @sec-solution-1), then the patient enrolment (see @sec-solution-2), add a Surveillance End form (see @sec-solution-14), fill in the data and then complete both the form (see @sec-solution-8) and the patient enrolment (see @sec-solution-4).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0016.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Patient Record Has a Completed Enrolment but no Admission Form {#sec-problem-details-16}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0016.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The Admission Form is a mandatory form that must exist exactly once for each patient admission.\n"
"It is usually created automatically, but like any event form, it can be deleted.\n"
"If the Admission form for a patient registration has been deleted, a new Admission form must be created and completed before the patient registration is completed, so that the data can be analysed later.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0017.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Day of Life Stored in the Form Does Not Match the Calculated Value {#sec-problem-details-17}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0017.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "The value of the day of life at the time of the event, which appears on some forms, is automatically calculated from the date of the event, the admission date of the enrolment and the day of life at the time of admission.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0017.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "If this error message appears in the validation report, we have determined that the stored value for the day of life is incorrect, which in most cases is due to the admission date of the enrolment having been changed after the form in question was completed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0017.Rmd:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please update the day of life value in the form (see @sec-solution-11).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0017.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "If at the same time the error message appears that the stored day of occurrence after admission does not match the calculated value, which is the majority of cases (see @sec-problem-details-18), you only need to perform the procedure described in @sec-solution-11 once to update both values.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0018.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Day of Occurrence After Admission Stored in the Form Does Not Match the Calculated Value {#sec-problem-details-18}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0018.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "The value of the day of occurrence after admission, which appears on some forms, is automatically calculated from the date of the event and the admission date of the enrolment.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0018.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "If this error message appears in the validation report, we have determined that the stored value for the day of occurrence after admission is incorrect, which in most cases is due to the admission date of the enrolment having been changed after the form in question was completed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0018.Rmd:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please update the value of the day of occurrence after admission in the form (see @sec-solution-11).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0018.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "If at the same time the error message appears that the stored day of life does not match the calculated value, which is the majority of cases (see @sec-problem-details-17), you only need to perform the procedure described in @sec-solution-11 once to update both values.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0019.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Infection Occurred Within the First Three Days of Life {#sec-problem-details-19}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0019.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "This message should not necessarily be interpreted as an error, but rather as a warning of a possible misunderstanding.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0019.Rmd:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As the purpose of NeoIPC surveillance is to monitor nosocomial infections with the potential for prevention in neonatal departments, early-onset infections generally cannot be recorded.\n"
"The NeoIPC Surveillance Protocol states that if an infection occurs earlier than 72 hours after birth, it is not considered a nosocomial infection and should not be included in NeoIPC surveillance unless it is clearly hospital-acquired (e.g. there is clear evidence of catheter infection).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0019.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "We have found that this protocol specification is sometimes overlooked and that some of our partners are recording early-onset infections, which can distort the reference data and their own statistics.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0019.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "We have planned to allow the recording of early-onset infections as part of NeoIPC Surveillance, but this will in any case be done in a separate event form in order to separate those infections with a potential for prevention in the neonatal setting from those whose prevention is more in the domain of antenatal care and obstetrics.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0019.Rmd:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please delete the forms for all infections that are not nosocomial infections according to the above definition (see @sec-solution-12) or adjust the infection date (see @sec-solution-7) or the admission date (see @sec-solution-6) if it was an input error.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0020.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Infection Occurred Within the First Two Days of Hospitalisation of a Referred or (Re-)Admitted Patient {#sec-problem-details-20}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0020.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Infections that occur within the first two days in referred or (re-)admitted patients are not considered to be nosocomial infections according to the NeoIPC Surveillance Protocol and therefore cannot be recorded.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_problem_detail_0020.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please delete the forms for all infections that are not nosocomial infections according to this definition (see @sec-solution-12) or adjust the infection date (see @sec-solution-7) or the admission date (see @sec-solution-6) if it is an input error.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0001.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Opening the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard of a Patient Record {#sec-solution-1}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0001.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "To work with a patient record or an enrolment, you need to open the associated [Tracked Entity Instance (TEI) Dashboard](https://docs.dhis2.org/en/use/user-guides/dhis-core-version-240/tracking-individual-level-data/tracker-capture.html#about_tracked_entity_instance_dashboard) in DHIS2.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0001.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Normally you do this from the [list of enrolled patients](https://docs.dhis2.org/en/use/user-guides/dhis-core-version-240/tracking-individual-level-data/tracker-capture.html#simple_tracked_entity_instance_search) by clicking on the relevant entry.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0001.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, this does not work for patient records without enrolment.\n"
"If you do have the NeoIPC Patient ID or other data that you can use in a search, you can use the [Tracker Capture search function](https://docs.dhis2.org/en/use/user-guides/dhis-core-version-240/tracking-individual-level-data/tracker-capture.html#advanced_tracked_entity_instance_search) to find and open the patient record.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block ({.callout-tip})
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0001.Rmd:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "For the records included in this report, the easiest way to open the dashboard is to click on the link we have provided under the corresponding NeoIPC Patient ID.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0002.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deleting a Patient Record {#sec-solution-2}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0002.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "To delete a patient record, first open the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard as described in @sec-solution-1 and then click on the 'Delete NeoIPC Patient' button that appears in the top right corner of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard of the patient record after clicking on the red button, as shown in @fig-delete-patient. If you then confirm the deletion in the dialogue that appears, the patient record will be deleted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0002.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "See also '[Delete a TEI](https://docs.dhis2.org/en/use/user-guides/dhis-core-version-240/tracking-individual-level-data/tracker-capture.html#delete_tracked_entity_instance)'.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0002.Rmd:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Deleting a NeoIPC Patient record in DHIS2](img/fig-delete-patient.png){#fig-delete-patient fig-alt=\"The \\\"Delete NeoIPC Patient\\\" button appears after you have clicked on the red button at the top right of the patient record's tracked entity instance dashboard.\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0003.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding an Enrollment to a Patient Record {#sec-solution-3}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0003.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "To add an enrolment to a patient record, open the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard (see @sec-solution-1) and click on the 'Add new' link (see @fig-add-enrolment). In the form that opens, you can change the pre-filled values if necessary. Then, click on 'Enrol'.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0003.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Adding an Enrollment in DHIS2](img/fig-add-enrolment.png){#fig-add-enrolment fig-alt=\"The 'Add new' button is in the middle of the 'Enrollment' block in the upper left corner of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard in the patient file.\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0004.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Completing an Enrolment {#sec-solution-4}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0004.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "To complete an enrolment, open the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard of the patient record (see @sec-solution-1) and click on 'Complete'. See @fig-complete-enrolment.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0004.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Where to find the \"Complete\" button in the enrolment form](img/fig-complete-enrolment.png){#fig-complete-enrolment fig-alt=\"The \\\"Complete\\\" button is located at the bottom left of the \\\"Enrollment\\\" block which is located at the top left of the patient record's tracked entity instance dashboard.\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0005.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reopening a Closed Enrolment to Make Changes {#sec-solution-5}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0005.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you want to change information in an enrolment that has already been completed and thus protected from changes, you must first reopen it for editing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0005.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "To do this, first open the relevant enrolment in the tracked entity dashboard (see @sec-solution-10) and click on 'Reopen' (see @fig-reopen-enrolment). Then, usually, the corresponding event form must be opened for editing (see @sec-solution-9).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0005.Rmd:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Since only one patient enrolment can be open for editing in DHIS2 at a time, another patient enrolment that is currently open for editing may have to be closed (at least temporarily) before another one can be opened for editing. To do this, first open the other patient enrolment in the tracked entity dashboard (see @sec-solution-10), then close it (see @sec-solution-4) and then open the patient enrolment you want to edit.\n"
"This step is not necessary for patient records that only contain one patient enrolment, and you can open the relevant patient enrolment directly for editing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block ({.callout-note})
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0005.Rmd:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The NeoIPC Surveillance platform permissions system includes specific permissions for reopening patient enrolments.\n"
"If the 'Reopen' button is greyed out or attempts to reopen closed patient enrolments fail, it is likely that your user account does not have the required permissions.\n"
"This is to protect enrolments that have already been fully entered and reviewed from inadvertent changes, but it can also make the process of correcting data more difficult.\n"
"In principle, the person designated as your hospital's project manager in the NeoIPC Surveillance cooperation agreement will always have the necessary permissions and can instruct us to grant or revoke these permissions for other members of your team.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0005.Rmd:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Reopening a closed enrollment to make changes](img/fig-reopen-enrolment.png){#fig-reopen-enrolment fig-alt=\"Screenshot of a patient record opened in the Tracked Entity Dashboards of the DHIS2 App Tracker Capture, in which the 'Reopen' button is marked with an arrow.\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the Admission Date {#sec-solution-6}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Unfortunately, because the admission date is captured twice in the NeoIPC Surveillance platform and used for a variety of internal calculations, correcting it after the fact is sometimes a complex procedure.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First of all, you must ensure that you use the same admission date in both the enrolment and the admission form. See also @sec-problem-details-3.\n"
"This means that any subsequent changes may also have to be made in both forms.\n"
"Depending on whether you need to change the admission date in the patient enrolment, in the admission form, or in both, you may need to take additional steps to update the internal calculations.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "In any case, you must first open the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard of the relevant patient record (see @sec-solution-1) and possibly also the corresponding patient enrolment (see @sec-solution-10).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "If the patient enrolment for which you need to change the admission date has already been closed, it must first be reopened. See @sec-solution-5. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the Admission Date in the Admission Form {#sec-solution-6-1}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To change the admission date in the admission form, you may have to reopen the admission form (see @sec-solution-9).\n"
"After you have changed the admission date in the admission form (see @sec-solution-7) and completed the form (see @sec-solution-8), you may also have to change the admission date in the patient enrolment (see @sec-solution-6-2).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the Admission Date in the Enrolment {#sec-solution-6-2}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:27
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To change the admission date in the enrolment, select the ‘Admission date’ field, enter the correct admission date using the dialogue that appears or the keyboard and confirm the change in the warning dialogue that appears (see @fig-warning-enrolment-admission-date).\n"
"Afterwards, you must update the calculated values in all event forms that have already been entered (see @sec-solution-11) and possibly also correct the admission date in the admission form (see @sec-solution-6-1).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block ({.callout-important})
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0006.Rmd:28
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"## Updating Calculated Values After Changing the Admission Date in Patient Enrolment\n"
"\n"
"The NeoIPC Surveillance Platform supports efficient data entry by automatically calculating some values when creating and editing forms.\n"
"Most of these calculated values are based on the admission date entered in the enrolment.\n"
"Unfortunately, DHIS2 does not have a function to perform these calculations even if the corresponding forms are not open.\n"
"For this reason, you must open all event forms that have already been created and update the calculated values after changing the admission date in the enrolment (see @sec-solution-11).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0007.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the Date of an Event in an Event Form {#sec-solution-7}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0007.Rmd:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, you must open the event whose date you want to change in the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard (see @sec-solution-15).\n"
"To change the date of an event, it must be open for editing.\n"
"If the event is grey in the timeline and has the status 'Completed', it must first be reopened for editing (see @sec-solution-9).\n"
"Once the event is open for editing (indicated by the yellow colour and the status 'Open' in the timeline), select the date field (see @fig-change-event-date; depending on the form it may be called 'Admission Date', 'Infection Date', 'Surgery Date' or 'Surveillance End Date') and enter the correct date using the dialogue that appears or the keyboard.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0007.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The field for the date of an event in the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard](img/fig-change-event-date.png){#fig-change-event-date fig-alt=\"A screenshot of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard, in which the field for the event date is highlighted\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0008.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Completing an Event Form {#sec-solution-8}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0008.Rmd:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, you have to open the event you want to complete in the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard (see @sec-solution-15).\n"
"Then click on the 'Complete' button, which is usually located at the bottom left of the event form (see @fig-complete-event).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0008.Rmd:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The 'Complete' button in an event form of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard](img/fig-complete-event.png){#fig-complete-event fig-alt=\"A screenshot of an event form of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard, in which the 'Complete' button is highlighted\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block ({.callout-caution})
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0008.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"## Event form validity check\n"
"\n"
"When you attempt to complete an event form, a validity check is performed to ensure that the data is complete and that no invalid entries have been made.\n"
"For infection forms, the NeoIPC Surveillance Definitions are also checked.\n"
"If information is missing or invalid, the form cannot be completed until this has been corrected.\n"
"\n"
"The validation process sometimes performs very complex checks which may contain errors. If you feel that the validation process is preventing you from saving forms with valid information, please contact us so that we can review it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0009.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Incompleting a Completed Event Form to Make Changes {#sec-solution-9}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0009.Rmd:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to change information in an event form that has already been completed and is protected from changes, you must first incomplete it.\n"
"If the enrolment has already been completed, it must also be reopened for editing before the event form can be incompleted (see @sec-solution-5).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0009.Rmd:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "To incomplete it, open the relevant event form (see @sec-solution-15) in the tracked entity dashboard and then click the 'Incomplete' button, which is usually located at the bottom left of the event form (see @fig-incomplete-event).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block ({.callout-note})
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0009.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The NeoIPC Surveillance platform permissions system includes specific permissions for incompleting event forms.\n"
"If the 'Incomplete' button is greyed out or if an attempt to incomplete completed event forms fails, either the patient enrolment is already closed or it is because your user account does not have the required permission.\n"
"This is to protect information that have already been fully entered and reviewed from inadvertent changes, but it can also make the process of correcting data more difficult.\n"
"In principle, the person designated as your hospital's project manager in the NeoIPC Surveillance cooperation agreement will always have the necessary permissions and can instruct us to grant or revoke these permissions for other members of your team.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0009.Rmd:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The 'Incomplete' button in an event form of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard](img/fig-incomplete-event.png){#fig-incomplete-event fig-alt=\"A screenshot of an event form of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard, in which the 'Incomplete' button is highlighted\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0010.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Opening an Enrolment in the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard {#sec-solution-10}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0010.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When you open the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard (see @sec-solution-1) of a patient record that contains an open enrolment, it opens automatically.\n"
"You can access other closed enrolments by clicking the 'History' link (see @fig-open-enrolment-multiple) in the top left corner of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard under Enrolment and then selecting the one you want to open from the history displayed by date.\n"
"If this link is missing, there are no other patient enrolments in the corresponding patient record.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0010.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "If the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard of the patient record you are opening does not contain any open patient enrolments, the history of patient enrolments will be displayed directly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0010.Rmd:16
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Please note that only one enrolment can be open for editing at any one time.\n"
"You will therefore need to close an open enrolment (at least temporarily) in order to reopen another one for editing (also see @sec-solution-5).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0010.Rmd:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The 'History' link in the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard, which allows you to access the history of patient registrations.](img/fig-open-enrolment-multiple.png){#fig-open-enrolment-multiple fig-alt=\"A screenshot in which the 'History' link in the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard is highlighted.\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0011.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Updating Calculated Values in Event Forms {#sec-solution-11}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0011.Rmd:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Sometimes changes to form fields (especially the admission date in the enrolment) mean that other automatically calculated fields need to be updated.\n"
"If the affected forms are completed and therefore protected from changes, the calculated fields will not be updated automatically and the update must be initiated manually.\n"
"To do this, reopen the relevant form for editing (see @sec-solution-9) and trigger the recalculation by clicking your browser's refresh button (the F5 key or CTRL+R combination will also refresh the page and trigger the recalculation in most browsers). The updated values should then appear in the relevant data fields. If necessary, check and update the remaining data fields of the form and complete it (see @sec-solution-8) and, if necessary, the enrolment (see @sec-solution-4).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0012.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deleting an Event Form {#sec-solution-12}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0012.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "To delete an event form, open it in the Tracked Entity Dashboard (see @sec-solution-15) and then click on the 'Delete' button, which is usually located at the bottom right of the event form (see @fig-delete-event).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block ({.callout-note})
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0012.Rmd:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The NeoIPC Surveillance platform permissions system includes specific permissions for deleting event forms.\n"
"If the 'Delete' button is greyed out or if an attempt to delete event forms fails, either the patient enrolment is already completed, or it is because your user account does not have the required permission.\n"
"This is to protect information that have already been fully entered and reviewed from inadvertent deletion, but it can also make the process of data cleanup more difficult.\n"
"In principle, the person designated as your hospital's project manager in the NeoIPC Surveillance cooperation agreement will always have the necessary permissions and can instruct us to grant or revoke these permissions for other members of your team.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0012.Rmd:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The \"Delete\" button in an event form of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard](img/fig-delete-event.png){#fig-delete-event fig-alt=\"A screenshot of an event form of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard, in which the 'Delete' button is highlighted\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0013.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deleting an Enrolment {#sec-solution-13}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0013.Rmd:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "To delete a patient enrolment, first open the corresponding patient enrolment in the Tracked Entity Dashboard (see @sec-solution-10), then click on ‘Delete’ (see @fig-delete-enrolment) and confirm the deletion by clicking on 'Yes' in the dialogue that appears (see @fig-delete-enrolment-confirm).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block ({.callout-note})
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0013.Rmd:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The NeoIPC Surveillance platform permissions system includes specific permissions for deleting patient enrolments.\n"
"If the 'Delete' button is greyed out or attempts to delete patient enrolments fail, it is likely that your user account does not have the required permissions.\n"
"This is to protect enrolments that have already been fully entered and reviewed from inadvertent deletion, but it can also make the process of data cleaning more difficult.\n"
"In principle, the person designated as your hospital's project manager in the NeoIPC Surveillance cooperation agreement will always have the necessary permissions and can instruct us to grant or revoke these permissions for other members of your team.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0013.Rmd:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Deleting an Enrolment](img/fig-delete-enrolment.png){#fig-delete-enrolment fig-alt=\"Screenshot of a patient file opened in the Tracked Entity Dashboards of the DHIS2 Tracker Capture App in which the 'Delete' button is marked with an arrow.\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0013.Rmd:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Confirmation dialogue for deleting a patient registration](img/fig-delete-enrolment-confirm.png){#fig-delete-enrolment-confirm fig-alt=\"Screenshot of the confirmation dialogue for deleting a patient registration in which the 'Yes' button is marked with an arrow.\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0014.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding an Event Form {#sec-solution-14}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0014.Rmd:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To open an event form, you must first open the corresponding enrolment in the Tracked Entity Dashboard (see @sec-solution-10).\n"
"Then click the '+' button on the right side of the event timeline (see @fig-add-event).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0014.Rmd:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The button with the '+' symbol on the right-hand side of the event timeline of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard](img/fig-add-event.png){#fig-add-event fig-alt=\"A screenshot of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard, in which the button with the '+' symbol on the right-hand side of the event timeline is highlighted\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block ({.callout-note})
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0014.Rmd:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Since an enrolment can only contain one admission and one surveillance end event, these two events can only be added if the enrolment in question does not already contain an event of this category.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0015.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Opening an Event Form {#sec-solution-15}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0015.Rmd:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To open an event form you must first open the relevant enrolment in the Tracked Entity Dashboard (see @sec-solution-10) and then select the event in the event timeline.\n"
"If an enrolment's event timeline contains a large number of events, it may include a Next and/or Previous button (see @fig-event-timeline-full) which allows you to navigate to the next or previous page of the timeline view to view more events.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Validation-Report/en/_solution_0015.Rmd:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The Next and Previous buttons in the event timeline of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard](img/fig-event-timeline-full.png){#fig-event-timeline-full fig-alt=\"A screenshot of the Tracked Entity Instance Dashboard with the Next and Previous buttons in the event timeline highlighted\"}\n"
msgstr ""

